casebody.data:
TIDEWATER OIL COMPANY v. Dennis F. WALLER. No. 6409. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. June 25, 1960. Covington & Gibbon, Tulsa, Okl., for appellant. Floyd L. Walker, Tulsa, Okl., for ap-pellee.

Before MURRAH, Chief Judge, and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed on motion of appel-lee, on the ground that the order appealed from was an order granting a motion for a new trial and was not a final and appealable order.
